item.title: Polly Toynbee
item.description: When Polly Toynbee arrived at The Observer in the late 1960s, she quickly concluded that she would make a useless news reporter. Hailing from a long line of well-heeled and highly educated liberals and social reformers, Polly surmised that she didn't know enough about the country she'd grown up in. Since then, Polly has worked in factories, hospitals and care homes, shedding light on the nature of work and class... Feed: https://feeds.captivate.fm/full-disclosure/

item.title: Late Night Linux – Episode 242
item.description: Rare praise for Mozilla as more extensions come to Firefox on Android, Fedora is coming to Arm Macs, a rolling version of “Ubuntu” appears, an unwise solution to the problem of funding open source, SUSE might be the baddies, LXD is forked, and more. Feed: https://latenightlinux.com/feed/mp3
